external_knowledge:
- 'Seedling applications' refer to newly created projects of type 'application'.;
- 'Garden of innovation' metaphorically represents the database where projects are created. ;
- 'Sprouted over the past week' means these projects were created within the last 7 days. ;
- 'Grown their leaves most widely' refers to the variation in dust scores, reflecting the diversity in activity or health. ;
- 'Standing tall by holding the most hands of support' indicates the projects with the highest number of dependencies. ;
- 'Dust score' is an indicator of project activity or health. ;
- 'Hands of support from other projects' metaphorically represents the dependencies a project has. ;

sql:
SELECT project_name, project_number, dust_score, status
FROM projects
WHERE status = 'Active';

